CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1776103864
OL,3,COver 60% of Australian children still
OL,4,Cusing social media despite under-16s
OL,5,Cban
OL,7,FThe majority of Australian children
OL,8,Fare still accessing restricted social
OL,9,Fmedia apps, despite the country's ban
OL,10,Fon under-16s, a new poll has shown.
OL,12,FResearch by the Molly Rose Foundation
OL,13,F(MRF) revealed that 61% of 12-15-year-
OL,14,Folds in Australia still have access to
OL,15,Fsocial media accounts that should have
OL,16,Fbeen impacted by the ban.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1776103864
OL,3,COver 60% of Australian children still
OL,4,Cusing social media despite under-16s
OL,5,Cban
OL,7,FThis means young people may be finding
OL,8,Floopholes such as lying about their
OL,9,Fage, using VPN's to change their
OL,10,Flocation, or using an adult's ID to
OL,11,Faccess social media accounts.
OL,13,FWorking alongside YouthInsight,
OL,14,FAustralia's largest online youth
OL,15,Fpanel, MFR polled 1,050 children aged
OL,16,F12-15 between March 12 and March 31.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1776103864
OL,3,COver 60% of Australian children still
OL,4,Cusing social media despite under-16s
OL,5,Cban
OL,7,FTheir research found that the biggest
OL,8,Fplatforms have kept the majority of
OL,9,Ftheir child users, with 53% of
OL,10,Fprevious YouTube users, 53% of TikTok
OL,11,Fusers and 52% of Instagram users still
OL,12,Fbeing able to access their accounts.
OL,14,FIt also concluded that half of the
OL,15,Fchildren who used restricted platforms
OL,16,Fbefore the ban say it has made no
OL,17,Fchange to their online safety, with
OL,18,F14% saying they feel even less safe.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1776103864
OL,3,COver 60% of Australian children still
OL,4,Cusing social media despite under-16s
OL,5,Cban
OL,7,FAustralia's social media ban came into
OL,8,Fforce at the end of 2025, creating a
OL,9,Fmandatory minimum age of 16 for
OL,10,Faccounts on certain social media
OL,11,Fplatforms.
OL,13,FIt is down to the tech companies to
OL,14,Fensure those under-16 cannot access
OL,15,Fsocial media accounts.
OL,17,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,18,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,19,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,20,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
